	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You don't need any extra logic, Genesis SRAM decoding is so simple for &lt;=16M games, basically the upper half of the 32M of game address space (all 16M of it) is decoded to the SRAM.
<br />
<br />Why do you think the game needs 128 kbit/16 KiB of RAM? They don't make chips that size... It's also very unlikely that an 8M 1992 game would use a 256 kbit chip, much less waste half of it.
<br />
<br />Most likely the problem is that your donor boards are wired for odd addresses (using /LDS) and this game uses even addresses (using /UDS), or vice versa.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


